news.title: Tata Realty secures Rs 825 crore from IFC to refinance IT park in Chennai
news.para: Ramanujan Intellion Park has achieved a complete reduction of emissions through renewables or carbon off-sets, saving more than 20 percent on water and embodied energy in materials while attaining over 42% percent energy savings on-site.

news.title: Bombay HC refuses to grant relief to 41 Vasai buildings facing demolition
news.para: A division bench of Justices M S Sonak and Kamal Khata, however, granted flat owners in the buildings time till September 30 to vacate the premises subject to submission of an undertaking to vacate.

news.title: MahaRERA acts against 628 projects for non-compliance with registration & QR code rules
news.para: To keep one’s investment secured, MahaRERA has appealed to homebuyers not to engage in transactions with housing projects without the mandatory RERA registration number.

news.title: Piramal Capital & Housing Finance plans to raise up to $500 million through dollar-bond sale
news.para: Billionaire Ajay Piramal’s firm is in talks with a group of global investment banks to raise $300 million to $500 million via such notes with a tenor of three to five years, the people said, asking not to be identified as the discussion are private.

news.title: Mangaluru civic body to conduct 3D digital twin drone survey
news.para: The purpose of the drone survey is to create a comprehensive databank of the city that will assist the revenue, engineering, health, town planning, and other wings of the city corporation.

news.title: Panel to study BIS guidelines for uniform building code in Gautam Budh Nagar
news.para: Noida Authority has recently made this proposal, months after the director-general of BIS, Pramod Kumar Tiwari, urged it to include provisions of the Standardised Development and Building Regulation, 2023 (SDBR-2023) in its bylaws.

news.title: INH Mauritius to sell its 49% stake in JMFCS to JM Financial for about Rs 3,000 crore
news.para: INH Mauritius, an investment fund managed by Pandit, will sell 49% in JM Financial Credit Solutions (JMFCS) - the realty financing business - to Kampani's JM Financial in a deal valued at about Rs 3,000 crore.

news.title: YEIDA withdraws plea at NCLAT against Ace Infracity bid for Three C Homes
news.para: Both YEIDA and Ace Infracity were in talks for settlement, while the matter was pending before the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT).

news.title: HDFC Capital to invest $2 billion in affordable housing segment by 2025 end
news.para: The world's largest affordable housing platform that counts ADIA as its key investor is in the process of achieving its medium-term goal of financing 1 million affordable homes in India through existing platforms set up with leading developers.

news.title: Madras high court orders authorities to issue free house pattas to 500 SC families
news.para: Petitioner P Selvakumar belonging to the arunthathiyar community said that around 500 scheduled caste families live in deplorable conditions in Teppampatti village.

news.title: NGT orders Ludhiana civic body to remove construction raised on green belt area
news.para: The NGT directed the MC to work under the supervision of the district magistrate and representative of Punjab State Pollution Control Board and asked the MC commissioner to submit a compliance report with the registrar general of the Tribunal within two months.

news.title: Chennai development body plans to build co-working centres in three places
news.para: In Chennai, these centres started emerging in early 2000 and picked up in 2015. They offer cabins with three-seaters and above, fixed desks, flex desks, and meeting rooms for people to choose from.

news.title: Housing prices in NCR & MMR surge 49% in five years: Anarock
news.para: Average residential prices in NCR increased from Rs 4,565 per sq ft to Rs 6,800 per sq ft between H1 2019 and H1 2024 while in MMR, average residential prices appreciated from Rs 10,610 per sq ft in H1 2019 to Rs 15,650 per sq ft in H1 2024, according to Anarock data.

news.title: Fire NOC must for buildings higher than 15 metres to get electricity connection in Delhi
news.para: As per Regulation No 10(7) of the principal regulations, the discoms may disconnect the supply of electricity in case a direction or order for demolition of the premises is passed by a Court, or DDA or MCD or Competent Statutory Authority, said the notice.

news.title: SignatureGlobal (India) reports pre-sales of Rs 31.2 billion in Q1 FY25
news.para: SignatureGlobal (India)'s collections in Q1 FY25 grew by 102% to Rs 12.1 billion. Net debt reduced by 16% to Rs 9.8 billion at the end of Q1 FY25 in comparison to Rs 11.6 billion as at the end of FY24.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government amends hotel building byelaws to boost tourism
news.para: Calling the move a ‘reformative step’, the spokesperson said: According to the government order issued by the housing and urban planning department, the Building Construction and Development Byelaws, 2008, have been amended.

news.title: Ronit Roy buys apartment for Rs 19 crore in Mumbai’s Versova
news.para: As part of the transaction, the buyer will get exclusive access to four car parking slots in the tower. He has paid stamp duty of nearly Rs 1.14 crore for the registration of the deal that took place on June 10, showed documents accessed through IndexTap.com.

news.title: U.S. developer Panattoni says India should ease land acquisition process
news.para: While India offers opportunities for expansion, "the biggest challenge is land itself - permissions (and) availability of data to acquire land," said Robert Dobrzycki, CEO of Panattoni.

news.title: JICA signs pact for final tranche of Rs 4,657-crore loan for Mumbai metro line-3
news.para: Department of Economic Affairs (DEA) additional secretary Manisha Sinha and Ambassador of Japan to India Hiroshi Suzuki signed the loan agreement.

news.title: Telangana government mulls land conversion use to raise revenue
news.para: According to sources, there was a huge demand for such industrial land conversion for commercial or residential use. The govt too hopes to net close to Rs 10,000 crore from such conversion .
